Sequential steps to create a Linux VM:

1. Go to Azure Portal
2. Select “Virtual Machines”
3. Click “Create”
4. Choose resource group
5. Enter VM name
6. Select Linux image (Ubuntu)
7. Choose VM size
8. Set authentication (SSH key/password)
9. Configure networking
10. Review and create

For example, deploying an Ubuntu VM for hosting a web server.

A real-life use case is developers creating environments for testing applications.

Another example is hosting backend services on Linux servers.

This exercise helps understand compute deployment.
